portauprince haiti ap a roman catholic priest on tuesday 
called on haitians gathered to honor a slain human rights leader to 
keep fighting against state terrorism 
lafontant joseph has left but he has not passed away 
father jeanbertrand aristide told about 1000 people gathered at 
st jean bosco church for a memorial mass 
joseph 54 a lawyer and political militant was found beaten 
and stabbed to death in his car july 11 police said 
human rights leaders called the murder an effort to silence 
opposition to the military government of lt gen henri namphy who 
ousted president leslie manigat june 19 and suspended the 
constitution 
the ministry of justice said the killing was a serious blow to 
the democratic process and that the murderers would be sought and 
tried according to the law 
a whole generation has indigestion from the corruption the 
army has sown said aristide a popular priest who heads the 
radical wing of haitis roman catholic church we must remain 
faithful to those who were faithful to the struggle against 
macoutism 
the word macoutism is synonymous with statebacked crime and 
violence 
no one has been brought to trial for the 1987 murders of 
political leaders louiseugene athis and yves volel they were 
killed when namphy was head of a provisional junta that governed 
haiti for two years after the flight of former president 
jeanclaude duvalier in february 1986 
joseph was buried saturday morning in portauprince cemetery 
before about 200 relatives and friends 
in 1978 joseph helped found the haitian league for human 
rights in 1986 he founded the center for the promotion of human 
rights which he directed until his death 
