<TEXT>
a day at the races became an affair of state in 
france when the government ordered a betting concern to pay about 
10 million to gamblers bilked of their winnings when a tracks 
tote board flashed the wrong numbers 
the office of premier michel rocard said people who had bet on 
the right horse at the maisonslaffitte tracks prix de strasbourg 
on sunday but went away emptyhanded would collect after all those 
who collected winnings based on the miscall can also keep their 
money 
the announcement came after a meeting tuesday between 
representatives of the budget and agricultural ministries and 
racetrack officials 
following the error in the announcing of the prix de 
strasbourg results the state considers that measures must be 
taken in favor of bettors who were victims of this situation the 
premiers office said in a statement 
the real winning numbers of sundays race were 148511 but a 
judge who scrutinized a photo finish inadvertently called out 
148115 and it was those numbers that went up on the tote board 
the error was recognized shortly afterward but too late to make 
reparations according to the racing code winning tickets are 
those which match the numbers on the tote board right or wrong 
officials estimated that the staterun betting concern will have 
to pay out about 10 million to rectify the error but some race 
track habitues interviewed on the evening news are already 
groaning saying they and many like them had thrown out their 
winning tickets 
bettors who won with the wrong numbers collected about 360 each 
</TEXT>
