police sealed all entrances to the democratic 
national convention shortly before the longawaited speech by jesse 
jackson on tuesday night blaming overcrowding in the arena 
tempers flared as a crowd of about 1000 delegates guests and 
reporters pressed against police lines trying in vain to enter the 
omni 
this is unbelievable said stanley watkins a jackson 
delegate from chicago and an atlarge member of the democratic 
national committee they should have known this was going to 
happen i think they should have had it in a bigger hall 
among those in the crowd outside the arena was sen sam nunn of 
georgia who had addressed the convention a short time earlier 
asked whether he was upset at apparently being excluded from the 
hall he replied i wont comment but aides said later nunn 
had intended all along to return to his hotel after his speech 
at first police ordered everyone outside the convention hall to 
head across the street to the world congress center where the 
proceedings were being televised on a large screen in an auditorium 
no one moved 
about a halfhour later the hall was opened briefly and about 
35 delegates were allowed in but other delegates were still 
waiting outside when the hall was closed again 
the omni is a basketball arena normally seating 16237 people 
but that capacity was cut to about 11000 when the hall was 
remodeled to accommodate the convention 
a city ordinance says people can be prevented from entering a 
building once it has reached standing room only said benjamin 
