<TEXT>
federal investigators are blaming the october 
1987 derailment of an amtrak passenger train in iowa on a workmans 
failure to restore a track switch to its proper position 
the national transportation safety board on tuesday concluded in 
its report that the accident occurred when a laborer parked 
maintenance equipment on a siding and failed to reset the switch 
for throughtraffic use 
two locomotives and 11 of 14 passenger cars of amtraks 
california zephyr collided with maintenance equipment on the 
side track injuring 15 crew members and 107 of the 230 passengers 
aboard 
the board also blamed the crane operator and a track foreman for 
failing to check the switch and criticized the management of the 
burlington northern railroad which owns the track for inadequate 
training of maintenance crews and not reducing the track speed in 
the work area 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
an air traffic controller from new york has 
been elected president of the new national air traffic controllers 
association in balloting that stretched over several week 
r steve bell is the controllers first union president since 
the 1981 strike in which 11400 controllers were fired and their 
old union destroyed 
bell who was hired as a controller after the 1981 strike 
received 1948 votes compared with 1138 for his chief rival fred 
gilbert of chicago 
the national air traffic controllers association was formed last 
year as a successor to the professional air traffic controllers 
association patco which went backrupt after its unsuccessful 
1981 strike the new union claims about 5000 members about 40 
percent of those eligible to join 
