burns and other hardline advisers it did not mean he would 
scuttle the treaty which limits us and soviet defenses against 
ballistic missiles 
it would mean we have a right to do something restricted by 
the treaty the official said it doesnt mean we are going to 
throw the treaty out the window 
in the meantime the treaty is due for its fiveyear review and 
the united states had proposed to the soviets that the review begin 
last friday in geneva 
