<TEXT>
here is the text of an iraqi letter from 
foreign minister tariq aziz sent wednesday to secretarygeneral 
perez de cuellar the unofficial englishlanguage text was provided 
by the iraqi mission and iraqi news agency 
your excellency 
i have the honor to refer to the recent development in the 
situation after tehran informed the un of its acceptance of 
resolution 598 
we need to move from the stage of generalities to the practical 
stage in which we could test the iranian position whether it is 
serious or tactical or which has partial or temporary solutions 
instead of reaching comprehensive and lasting solutions stemming 
out of our deep commitment to our responsibility toward reaching a 
comprehensive and lasting peace as soon as possible 
we suggest to your excellency and to iran the following 
practical steps 
motivated by a deep feeling of responsibility towards reaching a 
comprehensive and lasting peace as soon as possible iraq has 
proposed five practical steps to the united nations and iran 
1 holding of a meeting between authorized representatives from 
iraq and iran at the united nations headquarters to be followed by 
another meeting in baghdad and tehran later under the auspices of 
the un secretarygeneral or his representative to begin formal 
and direct talks on measures to enforce the un security council 
resolution no 598 in accordance with the sequence of its operative 
articles 
in case that a difference of viewpoints emerges on that it 
would be natural to resort to the un charter international law 
and the geneva agreement of 1949 on prisoners of war 
we call for a meeting to be held as soon as possible and our 
proposal to hold a meeting in baghdad or tehran besides the 
proposed meeting is aimed to create appropriate atmospheres for 
signing an agreement on comprehensive and lasting peace between the 
two countries 
2 in view of the importance of the shatt alarab issue which we 
had reaffirmed in our correspondence and talks with you mr perez 
de cuellar and the security council members and in our official 
statements we hereby request that you ask the specialized bodies 
at the united nations to immediately undertake the task of clearing 
the shatt alarab waterway for navigation in a manner which would 
enable the two countries to utilize it 
we also propose that these bodies should work out a specified 
timetable and provide the necessary possibilities to accomplish 
this task as soon as possible the two countries are also required 
to submit all assistance and facilities to these bodies in a 
constructive spirit in order to accomplish its task speedily 
3 iraqs full rights in free navigation in the arab gulf waters 
and the strait of hormuz should be guaranteed immediately 
4 while hoping to reach an understanding between the two sides 
to reach a speedy agreement for lasting and comprhehensive peace 
and good neighborlihood between the two countries as a basis for 
comprehensive peace inthe region it would be natural in case of 
partial or complete failure to reach this objective that you mr 
perez de cuellar and the un bodies undertake an active role in 
facilitating the task of direct formal talks and to provide 
viewpoints and advice which facilitate the task of the negotiations 
whenever that deemed necessary and the security council would 
remain having the effective role in accordance with its 
responsibilities under its charter to intervene in taking 
appropriate decisions whenever that deemed necessary 
5 iraq calls upon iran to refrain from intercepting or 
attacking ships and oil tankers operating in the territorial waters 
of the gulf states which are not part in the conflict and in the 
high seas and the strait of hormuz 
we hope that iran would respond favorably with these practical 
proposals and that you take the initiative in endorsing them and 
take the necessary steps to enforce them 
signed 
tariz aziz 
deputy prime minister and foreign ministers 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

