<TEXT>
thailand said wednesday it can no 
longer bear the burden of its cambodian refugees and threatened to 
move thousands to border camps within range of shelling unless 
western nations resettle them by aug 31 
the threat to move the refugees to the communist guerrillarun 
camps was announced by suvit suthanukul the secretarygeneral of 
the national security council the refugees are now housed at the 
khaoidang camp in thailand 
resettlement countries have known all along that thailand 
cannot bear the refugee burden indefinitely and we regard the aug 
31 dateline as an acceptable time frame under which all must 
quickly try to resettle the cambodians he said 
the khaoidang camp about eight miles from the cambodian 
border now shelters about 17000 people who fled the war in 
cambodia it is the only thai camp from which the cambodians can be 
resettled 
suvit said that starting sept 1 authorities will move any 
cambodians who have not been resettled to the site 2 camp next to 
the cambodian border suvit said the movement would be completed by 
the end of the year 
site 2 which houses 169000 people is the largest civilian 
camp run by the cambodian marxist guerrillas 
the camp is not far from the border and is still unsafe from 
border shellings suvit said 
western officials have opposed moving the refugees out of 
khaoidang the only refugee camp for cambodians not run by the 
khmer rouge guerrillas they say the new camp is too close to 
fighting between the cambodian rebels and vietnamese troops 
occupying their country 
a foreign ministry official kobsak chutikul said that 4000 
cambodians at khaoidang are likely to receive asylum by the aug 
31 deadline but many of the others have been rejected several 
times by resettlement countries he said 
the united states has accepted the largest number of cambodian 
refugees 
kobsak said the united nations is working on a program to find 
other solutions for the khaoidang refugees whom western countries 
are unwilling to resettle 
their future is their return to their homeland its time to 
puruse efforts in that direction he said 
