winpisinger president of the international association of 
machinists nominating jesse jackson for president at the 
democratic national convention wednesday night 
it is with a sense of a singular honor and consummate humility 
that i stand before you tonight to place in nomination the name of 
that one person in this vast nation of ours who has roused the 
moral conscience of the populace and our party 
the man who has shown us the way to thaw the ice of 
indifference smug selfsatisfaction and meanness that too long has 
masked the heartbeat of america 
the man who has ignited the fires of passion the fires of 
justice in our souls as no other contemporary has 
the man who has dared to sound our call to greatness 
he has brought us together here in the phoenix of atlanta amid 
the smouldering ruins of two decades of defeat challenging the 
democratic party to reclaim its heritage and rainbow identity 
he has brought us together on the common ground of conscience 
passion equality justice economic political and social justice 
for all 
he is the personification of feeling and reason united 
for him the struggle began the day he was born in the poverty of 
a small south carolina community nearly 46 years ago 
from that day onward he has been dedicated to shouldering aside 
the four horsemen of the apocalypse he has seized history by the 
mane and he is in the process of helping us leading us as we 
write a new chapter not only in the annals of american history 
but in the chronicles of humankinds long and torturous progress 
toward peace and prosperity for all in a global community 
look what this man has accomplished in a few short years 
</TEXT>
