<TEXT>
the british government said wednesday it intends 
to privatize the countrys water industry in a stock offering 
expected to raise the equivalent of 86 billion 
shares in britains 10 regional water authorities will be 
offered to the public in a single 5 billion pound sale at the end 
of 1989 said nicholas ridley the governments environment 
secretary 
ridley said the government has not decided whether it will 
retain a 49 percent stake or a smaller interest in the companies 
that will be created from the existing water authorities 
ridley said 28 socalled statutory water companies which supply 
water to the authorities will be allowed to convert into 
autonomous public companies when the authorities are privatized 
these companies currently operate under a range of legal 
restrictions 
french water companies and some of the british water authorities 
already have acquired stakes in the statutory companies 
prime minister margaret thatchers conservative government has 
sold off billions of pounds worth of stateowned companies since 
1979 it believes these companies such as british airways plc and 
british gas plc are more efficiently run privately 
it also has sought to get more shares into the hands of the 
public as a way of promoting capitalism 
