rain in the farm belt sent soybean futures prices plunging the 
permissable limit again wednesday on the chicago board of trade but 
analysts said a new forecast for a return to hot dry weather could 
end the slide at three days 
in other action on the board of trade oat futures fell sharply 
wheat was lower and corn was mixed 
on other markets sugar prices plummeted silver rose while gold 
